CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1776687066
OL,3,CStrikes by London Underground drivers
OL,4,Cto go ahead this week
OL,6,FRMT general secretary Eddie Dempsey
OL,7,Fsaid: "We have approached negotiations
OL,8,Fwith TfL in good faith throughout this
OL,9,Fentire process, but despite our best
OL,10,Fefforts, TfL seem unwilling to make
OL,11,Fany concessions in a bid to avert
OL,12,Fstrike action.
OL,14,F"This is extremely disappointing and
OL,15,Fhas baffled our negotiators.
OL,17,F"The approach of TfL is not one which
OL,18,Fleads to industrial peace and will
OL,19,Finfuriate our members who want to see
OL,20,Fa negotiated settlement to this
OL,21,Favoidable dispute."
OL,26,@oD@GOUvD@AOUyD@AOU}D@SO]
